<p>A professional and easy-to-use Laravel package for managing live streams, including routing, models, and automated installation.</p>

<h2># StreamPackage</h2> <p>Laravel package for managing live streams.</p>

<h2>## Installation</h2> <p><strong>1. Install the package via composer:</strong></p> <code>composer require vendor/streampackage</code>

<p><strong>2. Run the automated installer:</strong></p> <p>This command will publish your configuration and migration files automatically.</p> <code>php artisan stream:install</code>

<p><strong>3. Run the migrations:</strong></p> <p>Create the necessary <code>streams</code> table in your database.</p> <code>php artisan migrate</code>

<h2>## Configuration</h2> <p>You can customize the package by editing the published config file at <code>config/streampackage.php</code>.</p> <pre><code> return [ 'prefix' => 'stream', 'enable_chat' => true, ]; </code></pre>

<h2>## Usage</h2> <p>Access your stream dashboard at the following URL:</p> <code></code>

<p>To use the Stream model in your application:</p> <pre><code> use Vendor\StreamPackage\Models\Stream;

$allStreams = Stream::all(); </code></pre>
